5. Conclusions
The cooperation between the two audit bodies has proved its worth.
In this way, it was possible to obtain necessary insights into the systems applied in both countries: This applies in particular to: • intra-community sales, • risk management at the UST, in particular with regard to the selection of risky sales, • recovery of UST claims and • UST audit of large companies.
The audit revealed differences in the strategies for detecting UST fraud and in the systems explained above.
These findings can be used to improve existing procedures.
They can also be used to spark a debate among interested parties on which audit approaches and anti-fraud strategies can be used, such as the relationship within and between Member States and the EU Commission.
The experience and insights gained should encourage us to continue to jointly examine the administration of the UST in the future.
